sql:
SELECT pr.rating, COUNT(*) as ReviewCount
FROM product_reviews pr
GROUP BY pr.rating;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM product_views
WHERE view_type = 'detail page';

external_knowledge:
- "calm seas" metaphorically refers to categories;
- "average levels of inventory" represents the average stock quantity of the products in each category;
- "seas with no ripples" refers to categories that have no stock, hence their stock quantity is represented as zero.

sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM products) AS total_products,
    (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM categories) AS total_categories;

external_knowledge:
- "jewels" refers to the names of the products;
- "sparkle in the treasure chests" refers to products that are in stock (stock_quantity > 0);
- "electronics and clothing" are specific categories of products;
- "colors" and "royal houses" refer to the colors and brands of the products respectively.

- "items" refers to products;
- "number of times each item has been sold" corresponds to the total quantity sold;
- "most popular items" means items sold in larger quantities.
